            <thetext>IE&#39;s XSS protection doesn&#39;t like POST requests with JavaScript content. This can only allowed by changing a setting in IE&#39;s dev tools or by the server sending a special header, which jsFiddle doesn&#39;t do. So I can&#39;t see any better solution than to disable the jsFiddle links in all IEs :-(

Fixed with 3d22853 (master).</thetext>
